msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 30"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:0.5"
msgid "30. Rahonisajjasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on sitting in private"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pc30.1, pts-vp-en.2.300, ms2V_648
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato udāyissa purāṇadutiyikā bhikkhunīsu pabbajitā hoti."
msgstr "At that time the former wife of Venerable Udāyī had been given the full ordination as a nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.3"
msgid "Sā āyasmato udāyissa santike abhikkhaṇaṃ āgacchati, āyasmāpi udāyī tassā bhikkhuniyā santike abhikkhaṇaṃ gacchati."
msgstr "She often went to see Udāyī, and he often went to see her."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī tassā bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappesi."
msgstr "And on one occasion Udāyī was seated in private alone with that nun."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_649
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.5"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.6"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.7"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappessatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī sit in private alone with a nun?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.8"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.9"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.10"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.11"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappessasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you sit in private alone with a nun?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.12"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.13"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.13a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_650
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:1.14"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk sits in private alone with a nun, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-pc30.2.1, ms2V_651
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, ms2V_652
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "A nun:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.7"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "she has been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, pts-vp-en.2.301, ms2V_653
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.8"
msgid "Saddhinti"
msgstr "With:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.9"
msgid "ekato."
msgstr "together."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_654
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.10"
msgid "Eko ekāyāti"
msgstr "Alone:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.11"
msgid "bhikkhu ceva hoti bhikkhunī ca."
msgstr "just the monk and the nun."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-vp-pli4.69, ms2V_655
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.12"
msgid "Raho nāma"
msgstr "In private:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.13"
msgid "cakkhussa raho sotassa raho."
msgstr "there is private to the eye and there is private to the ear."

#. HTML: <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.14"
msgid "Cakkhussa raho nāma"
msgstr "Private to the eye:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.15"
msgid "na sakkā hoti akkhiṃ vā nikhaṇīyamāne bhamukaṃ vā ukkhipīyamāne sīsaṃ vā ukkhipīyamāne passituṃ."
msgstr "one is unable to see them winking, raising an eyebrow, or nodding."

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.16"
msgid "Sotassa raho nāma"
msgstr "Private to the ear:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.17"
msgid "na sakkā hoti pakatikathā sotuṃ."
msgstr "one is unable to hear ordinary speech."

#. HTML: </span></span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_656
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.18"
msgid "Nisajjaṃ kappeyyāti"
msgstr "Sits:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. REF: ms2V_657
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.19"
msgid "bhikkhuniyā nisinnāya bhikkhu upanisinno vā hoti upanipanno vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if the monk sits down or lies down next to a seated nun, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="gloss">
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.20"
msgid "Bhikkhu nisinne bhikkhunī upanisinnā vā hoti upanipannā vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If a nun sits down or lies down next to the seated monk, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.1.21"
msgid "Ubho vā nisinnā honti ubho vā nipannā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If both are seated or both are lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, pts-cs-bu-pc30.2.2, ms2V_658
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.2.1"
msgid "Raho rahosaññī eko ekāya nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is private, and he perceives it as private, and he sits down alone with a nun, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.2.2"
msgid "Raho vematiko eko ekāya nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is private, but he is unsure if it is, and he sits down alone with a nun, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.2.3"
msgid "Raho arahosaññī eko ekāya nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is private, but he perceives it as not private, and he sits down alone with a nun, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_659
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.2.4"
msgid "Araho rahosaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not private, but he perceives it as private, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.2.5"
msgid "Araho vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not private, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.2.6"
msgid "Araho arahosaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is not private, and he perceives it as not private, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc13, pts-cs-bu-pc30.2.3, ms2V_660
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.2"
msgid "yo koci viññū dutiyo hoti,"
msgstr "if he has another person who understands as a companion;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.3"
msgid "tiṭṭhati na nisīdati,"
msgstr "if he stands and does not sit down;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.4"
msgid "arahopekkho,"
msgstr "if he is not seeking privacy;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.5"
msgid "aññavihito nisīdati,"
msgstr "if he sits down thinking of something else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_661
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.8"
msgid "Rahonisajjasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr "The tenth rule, the training rule on sitting in private, is finished."

#. HTML: </p><p class="endchapter">
#. VAR: Ovādavaggo → ­bhik­khu­novāda­vaggo (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.9"
msgid "Ovādavaggo tatiyo."
msgstr "The third chapter on instruction is finished."

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection summary">
#. REF: sc15, pts-vp-en.2.302, ms2V_662
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.10"
msgid "Tassuddānaṃ"
msgstr "This is the summary:"

#. HTML: </p><div class="uddana"><p>
#. REF: sc16, ms2V_663
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.11"
msgid "Asammataatthaṅgatū,"
msgstr "Not agreed upon, gone down,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.12"
msgid "Passayāmisadānena;"
msgstr "dwelling place, worldly gain, and by giving;"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.13"
msgid "Sibbati addhānaṃ nāvaṃ bhuñjeyya,"
msgstr "He sews, a main road, a boat, should eat,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc30:2.3.14"
msgid "Eko ekāya te dasāti."
msgstr "Alone: those are the ten."
